author: johnh
msg: Disallow <script type="os/data"> nodes from <head>. Neko's parser, as of v1.9.13, explicitly disallows children of <head> to have child nodes of their own (except for #text), breaking os/data nodes in <head>.
As noted in discussion, there may be good reasons to allow os/data and os/template in <head> at some point, but at present it appears that nobody uses this at present.
